summary: This is an email from an assistant or paralegal to an attorney regarding a filing error in the case Times v. B01 3, 20-cv-833. The sender mistakenly filed a declaration without exhibits and then re-filed it with exhibits, resulting in two docket entries. The sender apologizes and offers to submit an explanatory letter to the court.

keyFacts: The document is an email dated August 6, 2020, regarding a filing error in the case Times v. B01 3, 20-cv-833.
A declaration was filed twice: once without exhibits and once with exhibits, resulting in two docket entries.
The sender offers to submit a letter to the court explaining the error or to discuss the matter further.
